  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0 (590c463 2022-02-18T23:15:29.668765+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge create\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (amd)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nFollowing the foundry book: [https://onbjerg.github.io/foundry-book/forge/deploying.html?search=forgeup](url)\r\nI tried to deploy a contract to Rinkeby using this command(constructor takes 2 arguments):\r\n`forge create --rpc-url $rpc_url --private-key $pvt_key --constructor-args \"x\" $admin src/Lootbox.sol:Lootbox` \r\nand it caused this:\r\n```\r\nerror: The following required arguments were not provided:\r\n    <CONTRACT>\r\n\r\nUSAGE:\r\n    forge create --rpc-url <RPC_URL> --private-key <PRIVATE_KEY> --constructor-args <constructor_args>... <CONTRACT>\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, when I do:\r\n`forge create --rpc-url $rpc_url --constructor-args \"x\" $admin --private-key $pvt_key src/Lootbox.sol:Lootbox` \r\ni am able to successfully deploy it. \r\nInterestingly, the forge book specifies to use --private-key after the --constructor-args but `forge create --help` puts it after that.",
